INLAND DEVELOPMENT COMPANY, a Corporation, v. The CITY OF OKLAHOMA CITY, OKLAHOMA, a Municipal Corporation, et al. No. 1413. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. April 8, 1936. For opinion below, see 9 F.Supp. 96. Rittenhouse, Webster & Rittenhouse, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellant. A. P. Van Meter, Asst. Municipal Counselor, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellees.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for failure to prosecute.
